File: Former ANC North West chairperson Supra Mahumapelo. JOHANNESBURG - The ANC is distancing itself from its MP Supra Mahumapelo's remarks on the Public Protector.
Mahumapelo told journalists the ANC won't support Busisiwe Mkhwebane's removal from office. READ: Public Protector standoff: DA welcomes Parliament's decision The former North West Premier also says Mkhwebane is doing a sterling job. The ANC says Mahumaphelo was speaking in his personal capacity. READ: Parliament gets green light on removal of Public Protector The governing party says it's yet to discuss and take a position on the matter. It's urging its members to subject themselves to organisational discipline. READ: Parliament pondering rules on removal of Public Protector National Assembly Speaker Thandi Modise has already approved a DA request to oust Mkhwebane. Mkhwebane is questioning the Parliamentary process to remove her, saying it's legally flawed.